snippet.description:
In the URL of each YouTube video is the 11-character video ID, unique for each video. Can they ever run out? Just how many videos can YouTube handle? To work it out, we need to talk about counting systems, and about something called Base 64.

Want to know how the single camera shot was done? "Matt Bought a DJI Osmo and It's Surprisingly Good" is today's video over on the Park Bench: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dyy41yAs8nc

I'm at https://tomscott.com/
or on Twitter at http://twitter.com/tomscott
or on Facebook at http://facebook.com/tomscott
or on Instagram as tomscottgo.

Filmed by Matt Gray, who's at http://mattg.co.uk
or @unnamedculprit on basically everything everywhere.
snippet.title: Will YouTube Ever Run Out Of Video IDs?

snippet.description:
How you can find your Youtube user id and your Youtube channel id fast and easy. This i great if you want to add annotations in your videos, or other tasks to promote your Youtube channel. 

Step one: Log in to your YouTube channel and click on your image logo in the top/right corner.

Step two: Click on YouTube settings.

Step Three: In the overview section you click on advanced.

Now you will find your YouTube user id and YouTube channel id under account information.

I hope this helped you and good luck.
Please visit my website http://www.waatz.com too sign up for my newsletter.

How Do I Enable Content ID On My YouTube Channel

0:00 If you are wondering why content ID isn't showing up green on your account after you're verified for partnership, stay tuned and watch this video and I shall reveal all.

0:19 Hi there, David Walsh here from DavidWalshOnLine.com and in this edition of 'Ask David' I'm going to reveal to you why content ID may not be enabled on your YouTube settings. Now, I've got a question from Kho, whose surname I'm not even going to attempt, so that I don't butcher it for them. But, they ask 'My content so, I need help. Hope to get your reply soon.'

0:44 Well, Kho, it's actually quite simple. All you need to do is wait for 30 days for content ID to be enabled. It's just waiting period that YouTube have. And once the 30 day waiting period is up you'll have the little icon appear on your channel
settings area, so you'll be lit up like a Christmas tree with everything else.

1:05 So, if you're waiting for that content ID icon to turn green, you probably only have
a few more days or if you just set up your channel, then you're gonna have about 29 - 30
days or so, for that to appear. So, it's just a waiting game for the little icon to appear
green.

1:20 So, that's the simple reason why content ID isn't appearing green on your channel. Now, if you've got a question about this or anything else on YouTube, feel free to just stick your question in the comments area below and I'll help you as best as I can to get your question answered.
